Maintainer: Stefanie Peschel <stefpeschel@gmail.com>
Description: Provides methods to approximate small p-values in permutation tests 
    using parametric tail modelling. Empirical p-values are combined with either 
    a Generalized Pareto Distribution (GPD) fitted to the tail of the 
    permutation distribution or a Gamma distribution fitted to the full 
    distribution. Optional support constraints ensure that no p-values equal 
    zero when the GPD shape parameter is negative.
    The package includes internal GPD AD and CvM critical value tables derived 
    from the 'eva' package (Bader and Yan; GPL >= 2).
